  "rationale": "A visionary neo-noir that prefigured The Matrix’s reality-bending ideas, Dark City fused expressionist production design, bold metaphysics, and genre-blending mystery. Studio cuts and weak marketing muted its impact on release, but the Director’s Cut reveals intricate world-building, imaginative visuals, and a probing exploration of memory and identity that remains fresh—making it a profoundly underseen cornerstone of modern sci-fi."
